# sequences_edit_smoke.numos — Phase 7A: edit a sequence expression and view the table.
#
# Unlike sequences_smoke.numos (which only opens the app on its default "Define" tab),
# this script proves SequencesApp is INTERACTABLE *through the numeric editor*: it edits
# u(n) from "2*n+1" to "2*n+5", commits it, switches to the "Table" tab, and lets the
# app recompute() the values so the rendered table visibly differs from default.
#
# Edit flow (focus starts on u(n), the Define tab, SequencesApp.cpp:55-56,68,100):
#   * ENTER (nav mode) opens the editor; startEdit() pre-fills the buffer with the
#     current expression "2*n+1" and shows it (SequencesApp.cpp:301-305,458-462).
#   * DEL removes the trailing "1" -> buffer "2*n+" (SequencesApp.cpp:409-415).
#   * Digit 5 appends -> buffer "2*n+5" (SequencesApp.cpp:419-435 via keyCodeDigitValue;
#     SequencesApp has NO digit-range bug — it uses the order-independent helper, not the
#     broken `code >= NUM_0 && code <= NUM_9` test, KeyCodes.h).
#   * ENTER commits via finishEdit(): _seqExprText[0]="2*n+5", then recompute()
#     (SequencesApp.cpp:307-312). recompute() matches the linear branch
#     sscanf("2*n+5","%lf*n+%lf") -> a=2, b=5 (SequencesApp.cpp:345-353).
#   * RIGHT switches Define -> Table; switchTab(TABLE) re-runs recompute()+updateTable()
#     (SequencesApp.cpp:454-457,261-269). u(n) column now reads 5,7,9,11,... and v(n)=n^2
#     reads 0,1,4,9,... Pure <cmath>/sscanf: no Giac/CAS, no PSRAM, no LittleFS. Fully
#     deterministic. (We deliberately edit only the numeric coefficient and never type the
#     variable 'n' — no key maps to it — nor touch the n^2 exponent, which recompute()
#     hardcodes; this keeps the edit inside a supported, deterministic branch.)
#
# SequencesApp has NO update() method and no cursor/caret blink, so the only volatile
# region is the StatusBar clock (HH:MM). This phase makes NO golden claim; the screenshot
# is a CANDIDATE for human review only (a clock mask is added by the human at promotion
# time, rect 4,6,37,13).
#
# Timing notes (deterministic, step-ms 16):
#   * 200 frames -> splash done, in launcher.
#   * 60 frames  -> Sequences screen load + fade settles after open_app.
#   * one frame per key command (1 command/frame).
#   * 120 frames -> Define->Table tab switch + recompute()/updateTable() settles.
#
# Run:
#   program --headless --deterministic --script tests/emulator/scripts/sequences_edit_smoke.numos \
#           --frames 800 --screenshot out/sequences_edit_smoke.ppm --quiet
# Exit codes: 0 ok · 2 script/parse error · 3 screenshot write error · 4 assertion failure.

log "sequences_edit_smoke: waiting for launcher"
wait 200

# Open Sequences (emulator launchApp id 7 — same id as the launcher's Sequences card).
open_app Sequences
wait 60
assert_app Sequences

# Edit u(n) from "2*n+1" to "2*n+5": open the editor, drop the trailing "1", type 5, commit.
key enter
key del
key 5
key enter

# Switch Define -> Table; switchTab(TABLE) recompute()s over the edited u(n)=2*n+5.
key right
wait 120

# Screenshot FIRST so the artifact exists even if a later assertion fails.
screenshot out/sequences_edit_smoke.ppm
log "sequences_edit_smoke: screenshot captured (Table tab, u(n)=2*n+5 recomputed)"

# Still the Sequences app after the in-app tab switch (tab switch does not change g_mode).
assert_app Sequences
log "sequences_edit_smoke: assertion passed (Sequences active)"
